00:17:12.760 --> 00:17:16.629
Jihoon: And proposals cut off at 11 seconds into the slot.

60
00:17:17.349 --> 00:17:26.809
Jihoon: And I think we should add another deadline for a tester's cutoff at, let's say, 12 seconds into the slot.

61
00:17:27.119 --> 00:17:31.489
Jihoon: This was found by Mikhail around 9 months ago.

62
00:17:31.930 --> 00:17:42.929
Jihoon: well, there is another deadline, which is 8 seconds into the slot, but as Nico pointed out nearly a year ago, I think this should be removed. This is just…

63
00:17:43.190 --> 00:17:46.100
Jihoon: Implementation-dependent example.

64
00:17:46.540 --> 00:17:51.670
Jihoon: So the reason why we need this new 12-second deadline is…

65
00:17:52.270 --> 00:17:59.370
Jihoon: to prevent split view among the testers, let's say there is an inclusion list, that…

66
00:17:59.670 --> 00:18:07.330
Jihoon: the block fails to satisfy, and that IR committee member actually equivocates.

67
00:18:07.970 --> 00:18:19.249
Jihoon: which, in turn, should make that block become canonical, but let's say that that equivocation happens at 2 seconds into the swap. So.

68
00:18:19.250 --> 00:18:29.269
Jihoon: Then, attester who saw the block before 2 seconds will vote against it, while a tester who saw it after will vote for it. So if

69
00:18:29.680 --> 00:18:39.870
Jihoon: Half of a tester vote for it, half of a tester vote against it, because they haven't seen that equivocating intellectualist, we're gonna have a split view.

70
00:18:40.160 --> 00:18:45.579
